    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>A Look at Extravagance</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Anthony Regina letter disputes Elizabeth Grossman's July 19 letter criticizing diners who spend large amounts of money in luxury restaurants</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>A reader, Elizabeth Grossman, thinks diners who choose to spend their money at a luxury restaurant like Alain Ducasse should donate an equal sum to a charitable organization (Letters, July 19). Why limit it to dining? Perhaps people who drive luxury autos when compact cars provide the same function, and people who wear designer fashions when Kmart clothing can cover their bodies, should also make charitable donations.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>A reader, Elizabeth Grossman, thinks diners who choose to spend their money at a luxury restaurant like Alain Ducasse should donate an equal sum to a charitable organization (Letters, July 19). Why limit it to dining? Perhaps people who drive luxury autos when compact cars provide the same function, and people who wear designer fashions when Kmart clothing can cover their bodies, should also make charitable donations.</p>
        <p>It seems that people get upset only when others enjoy a fine meal.</p>
        <p>ANTHONY REGINA  Brooklyn</p>
      </block>
